brainstorm on update feature
----------------------------


Client
=======

* mark each build with unique ID
* a build belongs to some line of releases:
	
	host name
	platform name
	branch
	

	eg. maya 2011/64x/stable
	
* update service can tell the unique ID of the build that is most recent for given line, which allows to answer "is my installation up to date?"

* sample request:

	<version-check>
		<current-install>
			<maya-release>2011</maya-version>
			<platform>64</platform>
			<os>windows</os>
			<version>1.x</version>
			<line>stable</line>
			<uuid>123456789012345</uuid>
		</current-install>
	</version-check>


* sample response

	<version-information>
		<current-version>
			<maya-release>2011</maya-version>
			<platform>64</platform>
			<version>1.x</version>
			<os>windows</os>
			<line>stable</line>
			<title>1.1beta</title>
			<uuid>123456789012345</uuid>
		</current-version>
		<links>
			<link url="http://www.neglostyti.com/yousuck/">home page</link>
			<link url="http://www.neglostyti.com/yousuck/downloads.php#platform=windows">download version 1.1beta</link>
		</links>
	</version-information>

	
Server
=======

* store relese info in database
* manage releases